  "overnight": false,
  "slug": "kimchi-fried-rice",
  "source": "This recipe is inspired by Roi Choi’s show The Chef Show, and [his course on MasterClass](https://www.masterclass.com/classes/roy-choi-teaches-intuitive-cooking).",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables. **Zucchini:** halve, and cut into 1/2 half-moons. **Kimchi:** roughly chop.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "On a large frying pan, warming on medium-high heat with olive oil, distribute the rice and fry until the bottom side is brown and crispy.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "On a second, smaller, frying pan with olive oil, sauté the zucchini.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While everything is cooking, thinly slice the scallions.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Once the rice is brown and crispy, turn it and fry until the other side is brown and crispy.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add kimchi to the zucchini and cook for a few minutes to warm up the kimchi.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add <Ingredient name=\"butter\"  /> to the vegetables, and stir until the butter has melted, remove the pan from the heat.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the zucchini and kimchi to the rice, add a bit of kimchi juice, add <Ingredient name=\"egg\"  />, reduce the heat to medium, and cook, constantly stirring, until the eggs are firm.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add more salt if needed, and serve topped with scallions.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
